Reasoning: The paper discusses machine learning and statistical methods for estimating parameters of interest in causal inference, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and statistics communities. The use of Neyman-orthogonal moment equations and the partially linear regression setting are also indicative of a statistical focus. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.STAT (Statistics), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are all likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of an explicit doubly-orthogonal estimation procedure for treatment effect, which suggests a focus on causal inference and potentially falls under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
